1
00:01:27,580 --> 00:01:31,930
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:34,950
[Episode 14]

3
00:01:36,479 --> 00:01:37,140
Paw Patrol,

4
00:01:37,590 --> 00:01:39,590
my trip to Shenchuan
was definitely worth it.

5
00:01:39,590 --> 00:01:40,789
At least, now it is proven

6
00:01:40,789 --> 00:01:42,229
that the article "Edward Scissorhands"

7
00:01:42,229 --> 00:01:43,310
on the Amusement Park website

8
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:44,840
is definitely a true story.

9
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,000
This is Wei Zhihua's QQ photo album.

10
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,509
Solid proof, isn't it?

11
00:01:49,759 --> 00:01:51,150
And do you know the password

12
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:52,680
to her private photo album?

13
00:01:53,310 --> 00:01:54,560
It is the date

14
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,680
when she and Edward Scissorhands

15
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:59,560
fell in love,
as written in Mister's experiment diary—

16
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,150
20110617.

17
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:03,870
Doesn't this prove
that Mister didn't make anything up?

18
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,350
A death was truly caused by him.

19
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:06,750
The details all match up.

20
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,880
This girl is dead.

21
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:09,240
She killed herself.

22
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:10,960
How are you not reacting to this?

23
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,420
I-Isn't

24
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:13,430
this enough to prove what happened?

25
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:13,910
Look.

26
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:16,300
[Support group
for victims of romance fraud]

27
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,090
Previously, the TV station

28
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:18,240
created this group chat
for victims of romantic fraud.

29
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,400
I've asked the admin

30
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,660
to send me all the victims' information.

31
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,680
A girl named Mumu caught my attention.

32
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,470
Her older sister had an identical

33
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:26,329
Medusa tattoo.

34
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:28,110
It really is the same.

35
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:32,450
That man, "Mister," is surely ruthless.

36
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,280
He alone could make

37
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,840
so many girls commit suicide for him.

38
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,240
What gave him that right?

39
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,000
I've reached out to Mumu.

40
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,720
Her sister, Xie Ke,

41
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:42,800
used to be a very promising figure skater,

42
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:43,910
who won

43
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:46,000
the championship
at the 5th Eurasian Youth Games.

44
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,840
But Mumu was too young at the time,

45
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:50,640
so she couldn't provide
much useful information.

46
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:52,280
That said, I did manage to get the contact

47
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,400
of her sister's partner.

48
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,660
He's in Bingyuan City.

49
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,150
Here's a reminder for you, though.

50
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,360
A police case has not been opened

51
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,460
or reported on this matter.

52
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:05,260
So, you're not going to Bingyuan

53
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,000
for an investigation, but just a fun trip

54
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,370
during the vacation.

55
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:09,190
Understood?

56
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:09,520
Understood.

57
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,850
Just a visit to friends.

58
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,170
[A fallen star: the tragedy
of a 22-year-old figure skating champion]

59
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,020
The year of 2011...

60
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:17,300
[A farewell in Chengyu Gymnasium]

61
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,329
Then the time of Xie Ke's suicide

62
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,550
wasn't far off from Wei Zhihua's.

63
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:24,710
You see,

64
00:03:26,030 --> 00:03:27,680
they both had that Medusa tattoo.

65
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,810
Could it be possible

66
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,750
that this tattoo

67
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,560
is somewhat a personal symbol

68
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,150
of Mister?

69
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,520
It's like a stamp.

70
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,240
When he stamps this mark on a woman,

71
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,240
that woman becomes his.

72
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,120
Why direct that gesture at me?

73
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,190
If that's the case,

74
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,910
Xia Yi actually had his victims

75
00:03:43,910 --> 00:03:44,870
get that octopus tattoo

76
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:45,360
f-following

77
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,840
Mister's modus operandi.

78
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,150
Y-Your hair...

79
00:03:49,910 --> 00:03:50,510
My hair...

80
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:53,030
It's fair to be called a work injury.

81
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,630
W-When I met the barber,

82
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:56,890
he immediately decided to give me a perm.

83
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,590
You made quite a sacrifice, didn't you?

84
00:03:58,590 --> 00:03:59,680
This is not so bad.

85
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,530
Is my hairstyle that terrible?

86
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,460
Keep yourself safe

87
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,740
when you're in Bingyuan.

88
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:07,800
Avoid getting injured again at work.

89
00:04:12,310 --> 00:04:13,040
Okay, got it.

90
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:27,870
Morning, everyone.

91
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:28,680
-Morning.
-Morning.

92
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,140
Here's something for you.

93
00:04:30,310 --> 00:04:31,310
My wedding candy.

94
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,510
It's Dr. Luo's wedding candy.

95
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:34,560
Who is the bride?

96
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,310
Why the rush?

97
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,070
We'll see her

98
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:37,070
at the wedding, won't we?

99
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:38,070
Come on, help yourselves.

100
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:38,870
Let's all share the joy.

101
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:40,530
Dr. Luo, when is your wedding?

102
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,480
My love and I both hate the hassle,

103
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,480
so we won't hold a wedding.

104
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,070
Back to your work, ladies.

105
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,270
It's time I started my shift.

106
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:48,310
-When will we get to see the bride?
-When can we see the bride?

107
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,310
I'll introduce her to you when I can.

108
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,580
Patient No.13, Xu Feng—

109
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:55,360
Xu Feng,

110
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,159
please report to Room 6.

111
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:05,960
What's wrong this time?

112
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:09,470
Actually, I'm fine.

113
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,260
I paid a registration fee just to see you.

114
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,650
While I'm at it,

115
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,920
I'd like you to enlighten me
on something, Senior.

116
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:20,650
Since when have you become this humble?

117
00:05:20,650 --> 00:05:21,810
I'm not used to this.

118
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:24,480
You've been saying
I don't know how to make a clean exit.

119
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,430
I used to...

120
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,010
object to it deep down.

121
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:29,780
I already made Li Changning
attempt suicide.

122
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:31,840
How did I not make a clean enough exit?

123
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:34,120
But recently, by chance,

124
00:05:34,270 --> 00:05:35,470
I found a PUA master's

125
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,950
secret manual,

126
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,970
and finally realized the huge gap
between me and him.

127
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:46,830
About encouraging suicide,

128
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:47,960
this is what he says:

129
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:50,170
the mediocre stab on their own

130
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:52,430
and inevitably stain their hands
with blood.

131
00:05:52,430 --> 00:05:53,510
Experts prepare the knife

132
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:54,600
and hand it over.

133
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,450
But real masters are able to

134
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:58,770
have their preys kill themselves
with the weapons on them

135
00:05:58,770 --> 00:06:00,430
and then walk away unscathed.

136
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,530
It's hard,

137
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,870
but not that hard,

138
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:04,130
to achieve this level.

139
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:05,430
It has to be known that a demon

140
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:06,950
lives in everyone's heart.

141
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:08,990
All we should do is release it

142
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,820
and let it devour our old selves.

143
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,370
Perfectly written,

144
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:14,580
isn't it?

145
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:17,630
Where did you read this?

146
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:21,530
People online all say
this master has gone into hiding.

147
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:24,130
All I could find were fragments
of his remarks.

148
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,230
What a pity.

149
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,240
See, he already discovered

150
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,080
the secret of manipulating others.

151
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,720
He could've enjoyed the ultimate pleasure
of being a god on earth,

152
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,510
brought benefits to his vast followers,

153
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:37,040
and received their adoration.

154
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,770
Why would he suddenly retreat?

155
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,520
Even his legends are fading.

156
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,380
Why did he quit?

157
00:06:46,690 --> 00:06:47,420
I don't know.

158
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:50,040
I don't understand a word you said.

159
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:52,220
You didn't pay
a registration fee of 600 yuan

160
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:53,820
just to tell me this, did you?

161
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,880
Ms. Yan's video has gone viral

162
00:07:05,010 --> 00:07:07,030
on the internet lately.

163
00:07:08,350 --> 00:07:10,300
Would you say her tragic story

164
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:12,680
is the weapon

165
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,870
you found on her?

166
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:15,550
Xu Feng.

167
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,620
If you don't have any other question,

168
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:23,720
why not leave and stop

169
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,450
hogging other patients' time?

170
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:32,550
I'm sorry

171
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,240
that I can't help you.

172
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:40,370
Thank you, Dr. Luo.

173
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:42,220
Every time after talking to you,

174
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:43,880
I can see things in a new light.

175
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,080
Sorry.

176
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,510
Please give us a moment.

177
00:07:59,510 --> 00:07:59,870
Sure.

178
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,280
I also found this.

179
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,490
This fee of 600 yuan

180
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,730
has paid for itself.

181
00:08:34,409 --> 00:08:35,940
Do you need my help to get up?

182
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,390
Medusa,
a monstrous woman with snakes as hair,

183
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:15,160
was originally a priestess
in the temple of Athena.

184
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,310
She swore a vow of chastity for life.

185
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,480
Yet seduced by Poseidon,
the god of the sea,

186
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,450
she turned into a debauched woman

187
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,710
having an affair with him in the temple.

188
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:28,120
From then on, any man who saw her face

189
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,450
would become stones.

190
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,600
Am I right,

191
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:32,750
Mister?

192
00:09:43,970 --> 00:09:45,720
I knew you'd come find me.

193
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,000
How did you get that photo?

194
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:57,280
Xie Ke's sister is as beautiful as her.

195
00:09:57,690 --> 00:09:59,030
As stupid as her, too.

196
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:01,960
I flew to Bingyuan,
bought her a bubble tea,

197
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,650
and she told me everything.

198
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:05,510
Besides...

199
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,820
She showed me this as well.

200
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:17,890
She strongly suspects

201
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:19,990
the man with a watch in this photo,

202
00:10:20,470 --> 00:10:23,470
just like the tattoo
that suddenly appeared on Xie Ke,

203
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,400
was a secret
that her sister couldn't tell.

204
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,150
This man was even probably related

205
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:29,910
to her death.

206
00:10:31,910 --> 00:10:33,670
Do you know which discovery excited me

207
00:10:33,670 --> 00:10:34,320
most?

208
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:44,440
In fact, upon seeing that photo,

209
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,100
I was eager to ask you about it.

210
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:47,550
But I held back the urge.

211
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,910
I also wanted to find out

212
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:50,640
if I was really inferior to you.

213
00:10:50,740 --> 00:10:53,360
Then I started searching everywhere
for that Medusa tattoo.

214
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,690
It took me quite a while.

215
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:55,760
Finally,

216
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,800
on an overseas online forum,

217
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,120
I saw someone mourning

218
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:02,140
for a long-closed pickup website.

219
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,150
There was a master

220
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,610
named "Mister."

221
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:08,220
He shared several

222
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,220
highly impressive PUA examples.

223
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,920
One of them was called

224
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,150
"The Snow Queen."

225
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:17,370
The master was you, right?

226
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,900
What a fascinating story.

227
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:24,850
You should write fiction.

228
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,880
How can fiction be compared with this?

229
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,010
It was a miracle that truly took place.

230
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,200
Too bad

231
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:38,970
that the genius
who made that miracle happen

232
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,520
doesn't even have the courage
to own it now.

233
00:11:42,230 --> 00:11:43,000
I heard

234
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,460
the Amusement Park was shut down
at its peak.

235
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,510
Why?

236
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:50,560
Wasn't it heart-breaking?

237
00:11:52,690 --> 00:11:55,420
I know what made Mister
close the Amusement Park.

238
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:00,940
It was fear.

239
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:07,180
When Yuan Ye stabbed me
with a bottle opener,

240
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:08,840
I felt fear for the first time.

241
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:12,090
You shared that feeling, right,

242
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,320
Mister?

243
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:26,780
[Lihai University
of Finance and Economics]

244
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:03,730
My mom is asking
when we can meet your mother.

245
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:06,200
My mom is a great fan of yours.

246
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:08,480
I hope your mother
will be happy with me too.

247
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:09,690
[Dial]

248
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:19,580
[Dial]

249
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:21,500
[Dialing]

250
00:14:21,530 --> 00:14:26,570
[The call is ringing]

251
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:29,730
[Call in progress]
[Lihai Mobile]

252
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:29,630
Hello?

253
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,240
Su?

254
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:36,000
Is that you, Su?

255
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,580
What happened?

256
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,300
What happened?

257
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,080
Su?

258
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:00,560
Su?

259
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:02,990
Su?

260
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:08,390
[Call in progress]
[Lihai Mobile]

261
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:35,410
Hello, Dr. Luo!

262
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,400
There you are.

263
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:39,830
Mom.

264
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,040
Where is your mother?

265
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:47,720
In the bathroom.

266
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:48,840
She said she felt a bit nervous

267
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,240
and wanted to freshen up.

268
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:53,360
What happened to your hand?

269
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:54,970
Nothing.

270
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,200
Just a minor injury.

271
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,150
A patient kicked up a fuss
about being discharged.

272
00:15:58,150 --> 00:15:59,430
But it's all sorted now.

273
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:00,280
Luo,

274
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:03,010
your job is quite dangerous.

275
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:06,280
Mom,

276
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:09,870
such emergencies are unavoidable
in our department.

277
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,890
But don't worry.

278
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:12,920
For the sake of Yan Ling and Jiale,

279
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:14,550
I will protect myself well.

280
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:17,710
Mom.

281
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:20,990
You're all here already.

282
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,600
Welcome.

283
00:16:22,630 --> 00:16:23,080
Nice to meet you.

284
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:23,750
Nice to meet you too,

285
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:24,440
Mrs. Yan.

286
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,850
This must be Jiale, right?

287
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,090
What a handsome little boy.

288
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,450
Thank you, Grandma Luo.

289
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:32,350
Just call me Grandma.

290
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:34,230
Thank you,

291
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:34,790
Grandma.

292
00:16:36,190 --> 00:16:38,650
I can immediately tell he's well-mannered.

293
00:16:38,810 --> 00:16:40,810
You've done a good job teaching him.

294
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,670
Ling looks even prettier in person

295
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,600
than in the photos.

296
00:16:46,350 --> 00:16:48,320
Don't you dare bully her in the future.

297
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,920
If you do, I won't let you off.

298
00:16:50,950 --> 00:16:52,550
I only have one older sister,

299
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:55,600
who got married and moved
to the Philippines when she was young.

300
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,200
Unexpectedly, her husband
passed away early.

301
00:16:58,270 --> 00:17:00,000
They didn't have any children.

302
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:03,200
Not long ago, she was diagnosed
with lung cancer.

303
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,750
and needed immediate surgery.

304
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,550
There's no one to take care of her.

305
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:07,200
So, today,

306
00:17:07,329 --> 00:17:10,510
I must apologize to you in advance
for not being able

307
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,550
to stay too long with you.

308
00:17:13,030 --> 00:17:14,560
Illness is no small matter.

309
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:15,859
Just go attend to her.

310
00:17:17,109 --> 00:17:18,109
I'm just sorry

311
00:17:18,349 --> 00:17:20,280
that I can't make it to the wedding.

312
00:17:22,030 --> 00:17:22,540
Mom.

313
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,589
Neither Yan Ling nor I like crowds.

314
00:17:25,589 --> 00:17:26,650
After discussion,

315
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:28,990
we decided not to have a wedding.

316
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,960
When Ling and Jiale
are on summer vacation,

317
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:31,920
the three of us

318
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,250
will go out on a fun trip.

319
00:17:34,870 --> 00:17:35,870
That sounds good.

320
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,050
As long as the two of you are happy,

321
00:17:38,050 --> 00:17:39,030
we are happy.

322
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:39,920
Right, Mrs. Luo?

323
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:40,920
Yes, sure.

324
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:42,320
Oh right.

325
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:45,350
You don't have to hold a wedding,

326
00:17:45,510 --> 00:17:46,160
but

327
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:49,010
you must accept this red envelope from me.

328
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:51,790
The amount is 10,001,

329
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:56,070
meaning that you're a one-in-ten-thousand
daughter-in-law.

330
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:57,000
Come on, take it.

331
00:18:03,910 --> 00:18:04,510
Thank you,

332
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:05,880
Mom.

333
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,030
Terrific.

334
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,070
Now I have a good daughter.

335
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,320
The moving company will come this weekend.

336
00:18:25,890 --> 00:18:26,820
Anything wrong?

337
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,700
You don't want to move yet?

338
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,250
How about I move in with you?

339
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:35,620
When we were dining just now,

340
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:37,570
your mother said

341
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,210
she wanted grandchildren.

342
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:40,550
But...

343
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:45,110
She was just saying it.

344
00:18:45,110 --> 00:18:46,370
Don't take it to heart.

345
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:50,340
Didn't we talk about this
before we got married?

346
00:18:50,540 --> 00:18:53,270
We don't necessarily
have to have another child.

347
00:18:53,730 --> 00:18:55,130
Jiale is all that we need.

348
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,790
I feel like none of this is real.

349
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:12,150
I'm so happy that it feels unreal.

350
00:19:18,050 --> 00:19:19,310
Then make me a promise.

351
00:19:21,130 --> 00:19:23,190
No matter what happens in the future,

352
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:25,910
you'll never leave me.

353
00:19:29,580 --> 00:19:30,710
You have my promise.

354
00:19:31,860 --> 00:19:33,120
I will never leave you.

355
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,000
Open the door.

356
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,720
Alright, walk ahead.

357
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:47,640
Be careful.

358
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:49,920
Get ready.

359
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,270
One.

360
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:52,920
Two.

361
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:53,920
Three!

362
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,200
This is so cool!

363
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,400
It's a space capsule?

364
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,920
Yes. When you sleep in this bed,

365
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:02,890
you'll be sent to the outer space.

366
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,170
Look,

367
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,930
the walls will be painted soon.

368
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:08,270
I've also ordered a desk for you.
It'll be placed here.

369
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:10,000
The workers can't be left

370
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:11,030
unsupervised.

371
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:12,560
I'll monitor them for you.

372
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:13,930
When the renovation is done,

373
00:20:13,930 --> 00:20:16,030
I'll move back to Yan Ling's apartment.

374
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:17,350
When you guys get too busy,

375
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,610
I'll look after Jiale.

376
00:20:20,170 --> 00:20:21,170
What matters most

377
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,750
is the two of you

378
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:23,980
living a good life.

379
00:20:25,310 --> 00:20:25,920
Mom.

380
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:28,550
Mom,

381
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:30,270
this is your home too.

382
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:32,240
You're welcome to come over anytime.

383
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:32,810
Okay.

384
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,450
Well then...

385
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:36,510
I'll go clean up the study
for Jiale to stay in.

386
00:20:36,510 --> 00:20:36,960
Okay.

387
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,640
I'll help Mom with it.

388
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:48,540
Mom,

389
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:49,790
let me help you with it.

390
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:50,270
Okay.

391
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:52,640
I feel like...

392
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:54,660
Grandma is a bit different now.

393
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:56,240
Is she?

394
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:57,550
Different how?

395
00:20:58,020 --> 00:21:01,300
When she saw me getting coke
from the fridge yesterday,

396
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:02,960
she didn't scold me.

397
00:21:03,380 --> 00:21:05,880
Instead, she replaced it
with a can at room temperature.

398
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,270
What are you laughing at?

399
00:21:07,270 --> 00:21:10,000
I'm just relieved
that you two no longer quarrel.

400
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:17,960
I've made peace with your grandma.

401
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:18,990
We...

402
00:21:19,590 --> 00:21:21,000
won't fight anymore.

403
00:21:22,590 --> 00:21:23,850
Better keep your word.

404
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:25,890
Come with me.

405
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,340
Let me show you one more thing.

406
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:30,890
Uncle Luo prepared it for you.

407
00:21:33,550 --> 00:21:35,030
Remove the cloth and take a look.

408
00:21:35,030 --> 00:21:35,830
You mean this?

409
00:21:40,710 --> 00:21:42,200
A mansion for Cola?

410
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:43,190
Do you like it?

411
00:21:43,350 --> 00:21:43,960
Yes.

412
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:47,450
I can put

413
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,560
a swing here.

414
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:52,920
But I don't want to move Cola

415
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,180
into this mansion until a few days later.

416
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:57,450
Why?

417
00:21:58,570 --> 00:22:00,170
Do you not like your new home?

418
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:04,580
I want to spend some days
with my dad at his place.

419
00:22:06,790 --> 00:22:07,450
Why is that?

420
00:22:09,510 --> 00:22:11,000
Now, both Dr. Luo

421
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,360
and Grandma are with you.

422
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:14,740
But my dad is all alone.

423
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:16,960
Even Ms. Fang Fang is ignoring him.

424
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,000
I feel bad for him.

425
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:26,490
Well, then spend more time

426
00:22:26,510 --> 00:22:27,480
with your dad

427
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:28,680
these days,

428
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,440
okay?

429
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:36,550
I'm sorry.

430
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:39,720
You're still a kid,

431
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:44,640
yet you have to always
take us adults' feelings into account.

432
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:46,030
It must be hard on you.

433
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:49,830
Actually,

434
00:22:50,350 --> 00:22:52,750
my dad and I haven't finished
that game yet.

435
00:22:53,820 --> 00:22:55,900
If Grandma sees us playing games,

436
00:22:56,590 --> 00:22:59,190
I'm afraid she'll go back
to how she was before.

437
00:23:00,110 --> 00:23:00,640
Will she?

438
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:31,560
[Introduction to Marine Science]

439
00:23:30,790 --> 00:23:33,600
Ling's father spent most of his life
at sea,

440
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:36,830
so she has loved going to the beach
since she was little,

441
00:23:36,830 --> 00:23:39,290
saying that it could bring her
closer to him.

442
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:40,720
When she grew up,

443
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:42,000
she also picked a major

444
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,360
related to the ocean.

445
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:54,670
This...

446
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:57,280
was a gift from Ling's dad to her.

447
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:58,570
She treasures it a lot.

448
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:02,610
It's so pretty.

449
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:06,830
Mom.

450
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,330
You finally woke up.

451
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,790
I'll put it on the bookcase for you.

452
00:24:11,790 --> 00:24:12,310
Okay.

453
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,070
Alright.

454
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:15,270
Take a rest. Enough with the work now.

455
00:24:15,270 --> 00:24:16,170
Food is ready.

456
00:24:16,270 --> 00:24:17,030
I asked Luo Liang to eat first,

457
00:24:17,030 --> 00:24:18,960
yet he insisted on waiting for you.

458
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:19,840
Yes, I did.

459
00:24:22,030 --> 00:24:22,770
This is for you.

460
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:23,270
It's hot.

461
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:23,810
Hot it is.

462
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:24,610
So hot.

463
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,030
Mom, take a seat.

464
00:24:29,420 --> 00:24:31,820
It's just the way you liked it
when you were a kid—

465
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:32,710
a soft-boiled egg

466
00:24:32,710 --> 00:24:33,710
without vinegar.

467
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,030
Does this suit your taste?

468
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:36,760
Let me try it.

469
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:42,370
It's delicious.

470
00:24:43,830 --> 00:24:45,790
It tastes exactly like when I was a kid.

471
00:24:45,790 --> 00:24:47,350
It's good. It really is good.

472
00:24:47,350 --> 00:24:48,490
Then have some more.

473
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:52,590
I heard from Jiale

474
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:54,640
that you make amazing braised pork.

475
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:57,140
I wonder
if I'll have a chance to taste it.

476
00:24:57,790 --> 00:24:58,590
Okay.

477
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,800
I'll make braised pork then.

478
00:25:03,370 --> 00:25:05,230
[Bingyuan City]

479
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:06,990
Come buy Bingyuan chicken carcasses!

480
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:14,430
Bingyuan chicken carcasses!

481
00:25:18,540 --> 00:25:20,680
Bingyuan chicken carcasses!

482
00:25:21,060 --> 00:25:22,030
Hey, sir!

483
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:23,380
Take a seat.

484
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:24,530
Qiu Dong!

485
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,740
Haven't you drunk enough?

486
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:28,000
Honey,

487
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:28,720
I wasn't drinking.

488
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,030
I was cultivating a customer base.

489
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:31,750
Can't you have a long-term perspective?

490
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:33,410
What long-term perspective?

491
00:25:33,750 --> 00:25:35,270
Look what you're like now.

492
00:25:35,290 --> 00:25:36,490
I'll be with you soon.

493
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:39,920
Are you...

494
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,110
Qiu Dong?

495
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:43,680
Yes, also nicknamed...

496
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,340
the Prince.

497
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:47,270
Care for some pork skirt?

498
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:47,890
Two pieces.

499
00:25:47,890 --> 00:25:48,440
Okay.

500
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:49,410
I'll take them.

501
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,270
Come on, let me fill your glass.

502
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:52,920
We just prepared a few dishes.

503
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:53,680
That's nice.

504
00:25:54,010 --> 00:25:57,460
[House specialty barbecue]

505
00:25:54,770 --> 00:25:55,750
Hey, honey,

506
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:57,870
my friend here came from afar.

507
00:25:57,870 --> 00:25:59,270
I must have a good chat with him.

508
00:25:59,270 --> 00:26:00,270
Okay. Eat up.

509
00:26:00,270 --> 00:26:01,000
Let me know if you need more.

510
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:01,440
Okay.

511
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:02,170
Remember it.

512
00:26:02,750 --> 00:26:04,210
Thanks for your hard work.

513
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:08,550
Come on, a toast to you.

514
00:26:07,430 --> 00:26:11,180
[House specialty barbecue]

515
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:09,770
Cheers.

516
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:10,880
Well,

517
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,280
when you called me earlier,

518
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,400
I thought you were a fraud.

519
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,350
Sorry about that.

520
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:16,210
I'll drink this up out of respect.

521
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,790
Ke's death

522
00:26:22,790 --> 00:26:24,210
was many years ago.

523
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:27,090
Has something new about it come up?

524
00:26:27,260 --> 00:26:27,710
No.

525
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:30,550
I'm just curious about

526
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:31,930
the competition

527
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,240
Xie Ke attended before her death—

528
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,100
the one you guys made a mistake in.

529
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,730
What exactly happened?

530
00:26:52,580 --> 00:26:53,640
It was all my fault.

531
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:57,880
I really wish I could apologize to her
in the netherworld.

532
00:26:59,370 --> 00:27:00,800
I don't know much.

533
00:27:00,830 --> 00:27:01,450
But...

534
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,240
aren't mistakes common

535
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,650
in figure skating competitions?

536
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:07,750
How was that one

537
00:27:08,310 --> 00:27:09,500
so serious?

538
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,240
Actually, before the competition,

539
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:14,480
we had a quarrel,

540
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,700
which affected Ke's mood.

541
00:27:17,480 --> 00:27:19,080
Because of the competition?

542
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,620
Because of her boyfriend.

543
00:27:28,010 --> 00:27:31,060
It was about half a year before Ke's death

544
00:27:31,230 --> 00:27:34,440
when I first found out
she was dating someone.

545
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:36,080
A company invited

546
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:38,070
our whole team to perform.

547
00:27:43,620 --> 00:27:44,200
Qiu Dong!

548
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:45,680
Hurry up!

549
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:46,000
Coach!

550
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,460
The bus is leaving in a sec.

551
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:50,480
Well,

552
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,000
Ke is catching up on sleep, right?

553
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,000
I'll hail a cab and go with her later.

554
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:55,110
Oh, you.

555
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,240
Off you go!

556
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,800
Come on, get on the bus.

557
00:28:00,770 --> 00:28:01,400
Bring my bag there.

558
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,070
Hurry!

559
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,030
She didn't answer

560
00:28:07,030 --> 00:28:07,570
my calls

561
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:09,640
or stay in her room,

562
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,490
so I went out to look for her.

563
00:28:12,830 --> 00:28:13,900
Are you Xie Ke?

564
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:15,620
Are you Xie Ke?

565
00:28:15,650 --> 00:28:16,270
W-Who are you?

566
00:28:16,270 --> 00:28:17,670
Can you please leave him?

567
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,500
What are you talking about?

568
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,340
You are Xie Ke, aren't you?

569
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:22,850
Get out of my way.

570
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,000
I am his girlfriend.

571
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,470
I really am his girlfriend.

572
00:28:25,470 --> 00:28:26,600
I beg you. Please...

573
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,500
Please don't break us up, okay?

574
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:29,310
That woman was

575
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,820
staring fiercely at Ke like this,

576
00:28:32,730 --> 00:28:34,530
as if she wanted to eat her alive.

577
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:36,030
I'm begging you.

578
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:37,240
Leave him alone, will you?

579
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,960
-I beg you!
-You're hurting me!

580
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:40,360
Give him back to me, okay?

581
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,960
-Get up.
-I've been with him for a long time.

582
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,480
I've abandoned my family

583
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:45,840
and even my child.

584
00:28:46,070 --> 00:28:47,400
All I want is him.

585
00:28:47,420 --> 00:28:48,510
He's all I want.

586
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:50,920
Give him back to me, will you?

587
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:52,640
But he really has never told me

588
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,640
that he has a girlfriend.

589
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,640
I truly am.

590
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:57,250
I truly am his girlfriend!

591
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,320
I beg you...

592
00:29:00,550 --> 00:29:01,640
Ever since then,

593
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,480
she started avoiding me on purpose.

594
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,200
At that time, we were

595
00:29:06,750 --> 00:29:09,000
preparing for the Asian Championships.

596
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:10,400
Except during training,

597
00:29:11,070 --> 00:29:13,000
she wouldn't say anything to do me.

598
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:21,680
Give me a minute.

599
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,240
What's wrong?

600
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:25,600
Are you lacking confidence?

601
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:26,680
I also think

602
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:28,680
this triple throw jump is too difficult.

603
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,280
Maybe we should play it safe.

604
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:30,810
Look,

605
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:31,590
I'll tell the coach

606
00:29:31,590 --> 00:29:33,030
about changing the choreography.

607
00:29:33,030 --> 00:29:34,110
I can do the jump.

608
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,100
You may go back now.

609
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,240
I'd like to practice alone for a while.

610
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,000
But this is a pair skating move.

611
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,350
How do you practice it alone?

612
00:29:41,350 --> 00:29:42,350
I can nail it.

613
00:29:42,350 --> 00:29:43,510
Off you go!

614
00:29:49,780 --> 00:29:51,150
Figure skaters like us

615
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,420
usually grow up together,

616
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,080
receive training together,

617
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,310
eat together,

618
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:01,700
and nearly spend every day together,

619
00:30:02,030 --> 00:30:04,090
except that we don't sleep together.

620
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:08,350
Plus, there is so much physical contact.

621
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:10,280
Her boyfriend

622
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:11,640
must've felt upset about it,

623
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:12,170
right?

624
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,260
Wait.

625
00:30:14,350 --> 00:30:15,750
That doesn't make sense.

626
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,400
He must have known it

627
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:19,440
before they started dating.

628
00:30:19,830 --> 00:30:20,830
If he said he minded it

629
00:30:20,830 --> 00:30:22,350
only after the romance began,

630
00:30:22,350 --> 00:30:24,610
wasn't he picking a fight deliberately?

631
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:29,200
I have a guilty conscience.

632
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:39,380
You might laugh at me,
but I'm going to say it—

633
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:42,440
I had always liked Ke.

634
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:46,790
I thought

635
00:30:47,830 --> 00:30:50,000
we were destined to be together.

636
00:30:52,110 --> 00:30:53,440
I had it all planned out.

637
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,760
When we won the championship again,

638
00:30:58,270 --> 00:30:59,800
I would tell her I loved her.

639
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:03,740
Who would've known...

640
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:11,040
So the two of you got in a fight...

641
00:31:12,010 --> 00:31:13,470
because of her boyfriend?

642
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:21,670
Before the competition,

643
00:31:23,010 --> 00:31:24,340
I saw her take medicine.

644
00:31:26,790 --> 00:31:27,650
What medicine?

645
00:31:30,430 --> 00:31:31,560
What are you taking?

646
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:33,880
Painkillers.

647
00:31:34,510 --> 00:31:35,070
For what?

648
00:31:35,310 --> 00:31:36,170
Period cramps.

649
00:31:37,110 --> 00:31:37,750
Why are you lying to me?

650
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:39,750
Are you even on your period these days?

651
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:40,680
As if you'd know.

652
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:51,450
Does this have something to do
with that guy?

653
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:53,000
Who?

654
00:31:53,890 --> 00:31:55,100
No need to hide it from me.

655
00:31:55,100 --> 00:31:55,960
I saw you talking

656
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:57,220
to that woman that day.

657
00:31:57,350 --> 00:32:00,160
Are you involved with someone
who's in a relationship?

658
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,110
I am not!

659
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:03,860
You'd better not be!

660
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:06,370
What is it with you?

661
00:32:06,750 --> 00:32:07,480
You're a brilliant young woman.

662
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:08,440
Why be with someone who's taken?

663
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,770
-Ruining yourself, aren't you?
-Stop it!

664
00:32:11,030 --> 00:32:12,160
You don't know anything

665
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,210
about him or me!

666
00:32:13,590 --> 00:32:14,550
I don't?

667
00:32:14,550 --> 00:32:16,010
You're right that I don't!

668
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:17,000
But I do know

669
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,000
even the greatest love
can't be built on someone's death,

670
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,730
for there will be retribution!

671
00:32:33,110 --> 00:32:33,720
Who?

672
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:35,480
Who died?

673
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:39,400
After the event,

674
00:32:42,270 --> 00:32:44,330
everyone but me went back to the team.

675
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:47,110
A few good friends came to visit me,

676
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,220
so I stayed an extra day at the hotel.

677
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:52,830
When I checked out the next day...

678
00:32:53,020 --> 00:32:53,710
Hello.

679
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:54,750
I'd like to check out.

680
00:32:54,750 --> 00:32:55,360
Okay.

681
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:56,940
I saw police cars

682
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:59,280
and ambulances at the hotel entrance.

683
00:32:59,280 --> 00:33:00,610
There was a large crowd.

684
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,270
I was told that a woman died

685
00:33:02,270 --> 00:33:04,070
in one of the hotel rooms.

686
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,100
Enough!

687
00:33:11,510 --> 00:33:12,960
I'll talk to him.

688
00:33:25,540 --> 00:33:26,400
How did she die?

689
00:33:26,830 --> 00:33:28,270
Was it homicide, suicide,

690
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:29,130
or an accident?

691
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:30,500
I don't know.

692
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,770
During those days,

693
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,740
I paid special attention to the news,

694
00:33:37,300 --> 00:33:39,360
but no criminal cases were reported.

695
00:33:43,110 --> 00:33:45,910
Do you mean Xie Ke didn't know about it
at that time?

696
00:33:49,310 --> 00:33:50,480
And that's where

697
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,350
my biggest regret came from—

698
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:57,430
I couldn't help

699
00:33:58,760 --> 00:34:00,890
but tell her about that woman's death.

700
00:34:01,350 --> 00:34:02,280
Upon hearing it,

701
00:34:03,950 --> 00:34:05,130
she was petrified.

702
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:07,930
Why did I have to be so tactless?

703
00:34:09,550 --> 00:34:10,670
Why couldn't I just

704
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:11,480
keep my mouth shut?

705
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,320
Why must I spill the truth

706
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,520
at that exact moment?

707
00:34:13,590 --> 00:34:14,550
I just couldn't zip it!

708
00:34:14,550 --> 00:34:15,230
I was so mouthy!

709
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:16,510
Why did I have to tell Ke that?

710
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:17,969
Stop. Don't act like this.

711
00:34:20,230 --> 00:34:20,760
You said

712
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,530
Ke took painkillers
before the competition.

713
00:34:24,219 --> 00:34:25,929
Did you know she had a tattoo?

714
00:34:27,590 --> 00:34:28,989
She didn't have a tattoo.

715
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,880
Yes, she did. She had one right here.

716
00:34:32,150 --> 00:34:32,960
It's Medusa,

717
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,000
t-the woman with snakes on her head.

718
00:34:35,550 --> 00:34:36,750
That was impossible.

719
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,190
Ke and I

720
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:39,760
practiced

721
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,719
the triple throw jump every day.

722
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,489
That spot you mentioned...

723
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:47,250
was where she took the most impact.

724
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:49,080
Why would she get a tattoo there?

725
00:34:55,210 --> 00:34:58,470
That is to say, Xie Ke made a mistake
during the competition

726
00:34:59,250 --> 00:35:01,630
not entirely due to emotional distress.

727
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,440
She took painkillers

728
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:06,150
because she had just gotten a tattoo,

729
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:08,170
and it hurt when you touched her.

730
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,350
Why would she get a tattoo?

731
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,130
An athlete

732
00:35:14,230 --> 00:35:16,780
can't possibly get such a big tattoo.

733
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,230
It wasn't her idea,

734
00:35:18,230 --> 00:35:20,410
but her boyfriend's.

735
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:22,240
Are you saying

736
00:35:22,670 --> 00:35:24,470
her boyfriend meant to harm her?

737
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:26,740
And she gave up her life

738
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:27,910
for a romance?

739
00:35:30,230 --> 00:35:32,030
I knew Ke best.

740
00:35:32,150 --> 00:35:35,270
She was not the kind of girl

741
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:38,000
who would go to pieces over love.

742
00:35:38,110 --> 00:35:39,230
In the eyes of outsiders like us,

743
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:41,360
she was probably just dating someone.

744
00:35:41,450 --> 00:35:42,670
But for Xie Ke,

745
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:44,590
what she had wasn't love at all.

746
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:47,440
Anyone chosen as prey by that bastard

747
00:35:47,710 --> 00:35:51,440
would feel nothing
but immense pain and torment.

748
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:53,960
Think about that woman.

749
00:35:59,890 --> 00:36:00,820
What do you mean?

750
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:04,920
She died too, didn't she?

751
00:36:07,140 --> 00:36:08,220
I get it.

752
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:12,670
He could push a woman
to the point of death.

753
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:16,180
Of course he could do the same
to another woman, right?

754
00:36:17,770 --> 00:36:20,200
Ke's death was actually caused by someone,

755
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:21,320
right?

756
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,920
Someone caused her death,

757
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:27,600
right?

758
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,360
Someone caused her death,

759
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,190
right?

760
00:36:30,210 --> 00:36:31,940
What do you think you are doing?

761
00:36:32,750 --> 00:36:34,080
Are you out of your mind?

762
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:37,560
If you don't want to be with me,
just say it!

763
00:36:40,290 --> 00:36:41,110
Look at you,

764
00:36:41,110 --> 00:36:42,440
lying on the ground now!

765
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:56,980
That was the story.

766
00:36:58,110 --> 00:36:58,960
Qiu Dong said

767
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,480
he felt he was completely responsible

768
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:03,280
for Xie Ke's injury at that time.

769
00:37:03,710 --> 00:37:04,960
So he proposed marriage to her,

770
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,560
with the idea of caring for her
for a lifetime.

771
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:07,790
But he was rejected.

772
00:37:09,670 --> 00:37:10,800
Shortly after that,

773
00:37:10,890 --> 00:37:12,350
Xie Ke committed suicide.

774
00:37:12,630 --> 00:37:14,560
If it hadn't been for that bastard,

775
00:37:15,550 --> 00:37:17,680
everything would've been different.

776
00:37:19,550 --> 00:37:20,400
Do you know which hotel

777
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,930
they stayed at in Bingyuan?

778
00:37:23,760 --> 00:37:24,320
Yes.

779
00:37:25,250 --> 00:37:30,000
[Xueyu Royal Hotel]

780
00:37:30,230 --> 00:37:30,960
I remember the incident

781
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:32,110
you're talking about.

782
00:37:32,110 --> 00:37:33,130
The woman was named...

783
00:37:33,130 --> 00:37:33,790
He Xiao.

784
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:34,960
She was from Diannan,

785
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,840
with the same surname
as the notorious ancient official He Shen.

786
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:37,550
Sir.

787
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:39,360
Did she have

788
00:37:40,630 --> 00:37:41,840
a tattoo like this?

789
00:37:43,030 --> 00:37:43,760
Yes, she did!

790
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:44,420
This was it!

791
00:37:44,630 --> 00:37:45,840
A head surrounded by snakes.

792
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:46,710
How scary.

793
00:37:46,950 --> 00:37:49,150
Now that you mention it,
I recall everything.

794
00:37:49,150 --> 00:37:50,870
Look, she was from Diannan.

795
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:51,960
But for unknown reasons,

796
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,590
she came all the way
to this very city of Bingyuan.

797
00:37:54,590 --> 00:37:55,800
Strange, wasn't it?

798
00:37:56,590 --> 00:37:57,550
Are you sure...

799
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,570
she died by suicide?

800
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:01,220
Absolutely.

801
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:02,400
At that time, the police

802
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:05,200
conducted a thorough investigation
in the hotel.

803
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:07,110
He Xiao came and booked a room herself,

804
00:38:07,110 --> 00:38:07,440
right?

805
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:08,590
After a few days' stay,

806
00:38:08,590 --> 00:38:10,590
one night, she went back to her room alone

807
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:11,840
and took her own life.

808
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:14,960
She wasn't seen interacting with anyone
in the course.

809
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,550
I was a server here at that time,

810
00:38:16,550 --> 00:38:18,920
and I had to go into her room
to change the sheets.

811
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:19,800
It was so unlucky for me

812
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:20,880
to run into something like that, right?

813
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:22,590
The police questioned me for a long time.

814
00:38:22,590 --> 00:38:23,630
Then what happened?

815
00:38:23,630 --> 00:38:24,560
What do you mean?

816
00:38:25,030 --> 00:38:27,230
Did her family not come looking for her?

817
00:38:29,060 --> 00:38:29,510
I heard

818
00:38:29,510 --> 00:38:31,760
her husband later identified her body
at the police station

819
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:33,710
and said he'd take it away the next day.

820
00:38:33,710 --> 00:38:35,800
But as the police called him again,
they found he had disappeared.

821
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:37,150
You have such a good memory.

822
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:38,480
It's been so many years.

823
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:40,230
The incident

824
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,020
and the way she died

825
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:44,150
were too bizarre.

826
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:46,520
Let me put it this way.

827
00:38:47,230 --> 00:38:49,290
The moment I pushed that door open...

828
00:38:50,580 --> 00:38:52,640
I knew I would never forget what I saw.

829
00:40:27,170 --> 00:40:31,360
[The Dark Romance]

830
00:40:41,990 --> 00:40:43,190
You want this, right?

831
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:44,160
Okay.

832
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,480
High-calcium milk for kids

833
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,400
made with premium formulas.

834
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:58,030
Free tasting.

835
00:40:58,030 --> 00:40:59,070
Come on, have a taste.

836
00:40:59,070 --> 00:41:00,070
Come try it, please.

837
00:41:00,070 --> 00:41:02,150
Haven't you acted
in any show lately, Ms. Zhang?

838
00:41:02,150 --> 00:41:03,350
Don't get me started.

839
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:06,230
I couldn't even get a single line all day.

840
00:41:06,480 --> 00:41:08,480
So I have to do some odd jobs now, see?

841
00:41:08,630 --> 00:41:09,680
But let me tell you something.

842
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:11,030
I feel like I'm getting
more and more relaxed

843
00:41:11,030 --> 00:41:12,280
and less and less nervous

844
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,440
during acting recently.

845
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:14,110
Really?

846
00:41:14,230 --> 00:41:15,180
Here comes a customer.
